definition: (literary) palanquin/sedan chair/to ride in a palanquin
a step/a pace/walk/march/stages in a process/situation

sentences.english: We'll walk over to the White House for a visit.
sentences.chinese: 我們步輦兒到白宮不雅觀賞吧。

sentences.english: We usually go to school on foot.
sentences.chinese: 我們通常步輦兒去上學。
